[30;1m33 | [0m[35m    The returned trainer can be used for testing the trainer itself and the[0m

[30;1m10 | [0m[35m    This extension changes an optimizer attribute in several steps, every step[0m
[30;1m11 | [0m[35m    the attribute will multiply a factor ``gamma``.[0m
[30;1m12 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m13 | [0m[35m    For example, suppose that this extension is called at every iteration,[0m
[30;1m14 | [0m[35m    and ``init = x``, ``gamma = y``, ``step_value = [s1, s2, s3]``.[0m
[30;1m15 | [0m[35m    Then during the iterations from 0 to (s1 - 1), the attr will be ``x``.[0m
[30;1m16 | [0m[35m    During the iterations from s1 to (s2 - 1), the attr will be ``x * y``.[0m

[30;1m100 | [0m[35m    A hyperparameter object can hold a reference to its parent hyperparameter[0m
[30;1m101 | [0m[35m    object. When an attribute does not exist in the child hyperparameter, it[0m
[30;1m102 | [0m[35m    automatically refers to the parent. We typically set the hyperparameter of[0m
[30;1m103 | [0m[35m    the gradient method as the parent of the hyperparameter of each update[0m
